The Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, in kwara State, has announced Prince Tunji Moronfoye as the new Publicity Secretary of the party in the state. Moronfoye replaces Tunde Ashaolu who died last month in Abuja after celebrating his 48th birthday. Prince Moronfoye served as the SA on MDGs under former Governor Bukola Saraki’s government while it lasted. He also served as Commissioner for Information and Culture in the second term of former Governor Bukola Saraki’s Peoples Democratic Party in Kwara State.